headline: Why Progressive Fell Today
summary: Insurance stocks were broadly under pressure on Monday.  In addition, the unrest in Los Angeles may have auto and property insurers further under pressure.  Shares of auto insurance leader Progressive (NYSE: PGR) fell today, down by as much as 4.7% at its lows, before recovering to a 2.9% decline on the day.
